                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1r" facs="001"/><desc>Crude drawings</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#147v" facs="148"/><desc>(including an <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1082Angel"/> with drawn <term key="sword"/>, drawn in black and red ink)</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r" facs="002"> f. 1v-2r, top</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                      <title type="complete" ref="LIT3509Epistle"/>, written in a different hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#147r" facs="147"/>
                    <desc type="Asmat">
                    Asmat prayer to Archangel Rufa’el for safety in childbirth, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ ሶበ፡ ትወልድ፡ ብእሲት፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="001"/>
                    <desc>
                    Despite the label, the Weiner collection number should be 467 and not 464
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#Inside front cover" facs="001"/>
                    <desc>
                    Note: mirror niche in inside front cover. Mirror intact
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#Back cover" facs="148"/>
                    <desc>
                    Colorful cloth is visible between the paste downs of the back cover
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#2r" facs="002"> f. 2r, bottom</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Copy of letter, in Amharic, from <foreign xml:lang="am">ከሜቴ፡ ወይዘሮ፡ ታፈሰች፡ ፋሩስ፡ to ለመርጄታ ገብረ ሚካኤል፡</foreign> asking for prayer and (financial?) support
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#2r" facs="002"> f. 2r, bottom two lines</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    note of secondary ownership, written in a different hand: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፊታውራሪ፡ ውብነህ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a5">
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="003"> f. 2v, top</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Writing exercise, copying the introductory prayer to the <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/> on <locus target="#3r" facs="003"/>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a6">
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="003"> f. 2v, middle</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Scribal note of commencing the writing of a letter for several persons: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልጅ ውብነህ፡, ግራዝማች፡ አባይ, and ፡ፊታውራሪ ፡ አብርሃ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="003"> f. 2v, bottom</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Genealogical note about three generations: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደጃዝማች፡ ኪሮስ፡, ግራዝማች፡ ፋሩስ፡</foreign>, and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደጃዝማች፡ ደበብ፡</foreign>.  The writer of the note is <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልጅ ነጋሽ.</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <desc>
                    The fourth biblical canticle is the Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a9">
                    <locus from="131r" facs="131"> f. 131r, bottom five lines</locus><locus to="131v"/>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Scribal doxology mentioning original owner, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተክለ ሃይማኖት</foreign>, and his wife, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወለተ መድኃን</foreign>, his children, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ ማርያም, ገብረ ሥላሴ, ወለተ ማርያም</foreign>,  his father, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስይፈ ሚክኤል</foreign>, and his mother, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ትውክልተ ሚካኤል</foreign>, and his brother, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዛማርያም</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a10">
                    <desc>
                      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2509Weddas"/> are laid out beginning on Monday and culminating on Sunday
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a11">
                    <locus target="#146v" facs="147"/>
                    <desc>
                    Scribal comment: Man began, God will finish
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a12">
                    <locus target="#146v" facs="147"> f. 146v, col. 1, bottom</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Colophon: This book belongs to <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወይዘሮ፡ ታፈሰጭ፡ ሰበይቲ፡ ባራባራስ፡ ሀጎስ፡</foreign>, mentioning her children,  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ደስታ፡ ወለተ ማርያም፡,  ራያ፡ ገብረ፡ ማርያም፡,  ውብነኽ፡ ገብረ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>, her father, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ግራዝማች፡ ፋሪስ፡</foreign>, and her brothers, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ግራዝማች፡ አባይ፡</foreign> , and <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልጅ አብ[ር]ሃ፡</foreign>, whose baptismal name is <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡</foreign>.  The name of the scribe is mentioned, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አለቃ፡ መሸ፡ ዘየጁ</foreign> (from Yajju), baptismal name <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ ማርያም</foreign>, “who deserves two mules,” the payment for the book, from (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ባራባራስ፡) ሀጎስ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a13">
                    <locus target="#147r" facs="147"> f. 147r, col. 2, last seven lines</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Beginning of a letter from <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወይዘሮ፡ደስታ፡</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
